President Trump welcomed Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue to the White House and congratulated him on his recent appointment. Trump expressed his commitment to supporting America's farmers and ranchers and discussed the need to eliminate unnecessary regulations that hinder their success. He also addressed trade issues with Canada, particularly regarding dairy products and lumber, and emphasized his determination to protect American farmers. Trump signed an executive order promoting agriculture and rural prosperity, and stated that the wall along the US-Mexico border will be built to address issues such as drug trafficking and illegal immigration. He assured that plans and preparations for the wall are already underway.